Also state the worst-case and best-case time complexity.

Consider the following algorithm that searches for an element x in a sorted array using binary search:

int binarySearch(int arr[], int l, int r, int x) {
    while (l <= r) {
        int mid = l + (r - l) / 2;
        if (arr[mid] == x)
            return mid;
        if (arr[mid] < x)
            l = mid + 1;
        else
            r = mid - 1;
    }
    return -1;
}

Analyze and derive the time complexity for:
(a) Best case
(b) Worst case
(c) Average case
Also draw the recurrence tree for the worst case.
